						<summary>

						<p>Door-jamb, proper right, of the Muktīśavara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1691, Sarvadhārin, Māgha śu. 15</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1769 A.D. February 20, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the completion of the <hi rend="italic">garbhagṛiha</hi> and <hi rend="italic">antarāḷika</hi> of the temple of Mukteśvara on the date specified. Registers a gift of one <hi rend="italic">Kuñcha</hi> of land in Mōkshaguṇḍam to god Sāṁbaśiva by Tāḍicherla Veṅkaṭanarasu for conducting food offerings and perpetual lamp on the occasion of <hi rend="italic">Śivarātri</hi> to the god.</p>						

						</summary>
